   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">

            
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604742_1831-02_page02.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#1-North-Audley-Street_ENK">
                     N<hi rend= "superscript">o</hi>. 1 North Audley Street
                  </placeName><lb/>
                  <date when="1831-02-04">
                     <del><unclear></unclear></del> Friday
                     4.<hi rend= "superscript">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Feb<hi rend= "superscript">y</hi></abbr><reg>February</reg></choice></date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  Gentlemen<lb/>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I was at dinner when the arm<lb/>
               chair you sent arrived and<lb/>
               I could not then examine it<lb/></p>
               <p>I observe that it is not<lb/>
               a chair newly made for<lb/>
               me as bespoke, deeper than<lb/>
               that which I sat in at your<lb/>
               house; but on the contrary<lb/>
               I think it is <unclear>the</unclear> very same to<lb/>
               which I objected as not being<lb/>
               sufficiently deep when used<lb/>
               with a cushion<lb/></p>
               <p>I will keep it however<lb/>
               upon condition that the<lb/>
               cushion is not charged<lb/>
               to me - the cushion being<lb/>
               absolutely useless —<lb/></p>
               <p>Also I must beg that you<lb/>
               will send for the chair to<lb/>
               have silk twist put round<lb/>

               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604742_1831-02_page03.jpg"/>
               
               <del>the seat</del> at <add>the</add> bottom &amp; top<lb/>
               of the seat as it looks<lb/>
               quite bare &amp; unfinished<lb/>
               at present<lb/>
                  <note>drawing of chair seat</note><lb/>
               If it would be any <choice><orig>conve<lb/>
                  nience</orig><reg>convenience</reg></choice> to you to send<lb/>
               a work woman or man<lb/>
               to the house to fasten<lb/>
               the twist on here you<lb/>
               are welcome to do so<lb/>
               instead of sending for<lb/>
               the chair<lb/></p>
               <p>Remember that I<lb/>
               expect to have the round<lb/>
               
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604742_1831-02_page04.jpg"/>
               
               table I bespoke sent <unclear>ho<gap></gap></unclear><lb/>
               on Saturday - and<lb/>
               the same time. I beg to have<lb/>
               my account with you<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               I am Gentlemen<lb/>
               Your <choice><abbr>Obed.<hi rend= "superscript">t</hi>.</abbr><reg>Obedient</reg></choice> <choice><abbr>Serv<hi rend= "superscript">t</hi></abbr><reg>Servant</reg></choice><lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/>
               <lb/></closer>
            <closer>
               <address><addrLine>To</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Mess<hi rend= "superscript">rs</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#FrancW1">France</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#FrancW1">France</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BantT1">Banting</persName></addrLine>
                  <addrLine><placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Pall-Mall_ENK">Pall <unclear>Mall</unclear></placeName></addrLine>
               </address>
            </closer>

            
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604742_1831-02_page01.jpg"/>
            <closer>
            
            <stamp><unclear>M</unclear>.EVEN <unclear>4</unclear>
               <date when="1831-02-04">4.FE<lb/>
                  1831</date><lb/></stamp>

               Miss Edgeworth<lb/>
               <date when="1831-02-04"><choice><abbr>Feb</abbr><reg>February</reg></choice> 4/31</date><lb/>
               <stamp>Portland</stamp>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>Mess.<hi rend= "superscript">rs</hi> <persName ref="./Personography.xml#FrancW1">France</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BantT1">Banting</persName></addrLine>
                  <addrLine><placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Pall-Mall_ENK">Pall Mall</placeName></addrLine>
               </address>
